post_cb({"26976651": {"ParentId": "26976567", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>The C++ standard says:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_26976567_26976651_0\">\u00a7 8.4.1/2 <em>[..]</em> A function shall be defined only in namespace or\n  class scope.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>So what you're doing is simply not allowed.</p>\n", "Id": "26976651", "PostTypeId": "2", "OwnerDisplayName": "user3920237", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2014-11-17T15:59:07.940", "LastActivityDate": "2014-11-17T15:59:07.940"}, "26976567": {"CommentCount": "3", "ViewCount": "967", "PostTypeId": "1", "ClosedDate": "2014-11-17T17:43:23.380", "LastEditorUserId": "2296458", "CreationDate": "2014-11-17T15:53:46.913", "LastActivityDate": "2014-11-17T16:01:53.527", "Title": "Function definition not allowed here?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "26976701", "LastEditDate": "2014-11-17T15:57:10.160", "Id": "26976567", "Score": "-1", "Body": "<p>i am a total newbie to c++.\ni am writing this function but somehow it give me this error</p>\n<pre><code>Error: a function-definition is not allowed here before '{' token\n</code></pre>\n<p>My code is</p>\n<pre><code>int main() {\n    //number is given num\n    // power is raise to power\n    int raiseTo(int number, int power)\n    {\n        for (int i=0;i&lt;=power;i++)\n        {       \n            number=number*number;\n        }\n        return number;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Please tell me what i am doing wrong. thanks.</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++>", "OwnerUserId": "2729887", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "26976701": {"ParentId": "26976567", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>Two major problems:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>You should not implement a function inside a function</li>\n<li>You are not performing the power algorithm correctly</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Try this code instead:</p>\n<pre><code>int raiseTo(int number,int power)\n{\n    int result = 1;\n    for (int i=0; i&lt;power; i++)\n    {\n        result = result*number;\n    }\n    return result;\n}\n\nint main()\n{\n    int x = 2;\n    int y = 3;\n    int z = raiseTo(x,y);\n    printf(\"%d^%d = %d\\n\",x,y,z);\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1382251", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "26976701", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2014-11-17T16:01:53.527", "LastActivityDate": "2014-11-17T16:01:53.527"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_26976567_26976651_0": {"section_id": 3263, "quality": 0.8333333333333334, "length": 5}}, "n3337": {"so_26976567_26976651_0": {"section_id": 3135, "quality": 0.8333333333333334, "length": 5}}, "n4659": {"so_26976567_26976651_0": {"section_id": 4021, "quality": 0.8333333333333334, "length": 5}}}});